This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new paradigm for discovering disentangled representations of class structure using a novel loss function. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on recall@$k$ and few-shot learning tasks, which are common evaluation metrics in machine learning. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it aims to obtain more interpretable and manipulable deep representations of concepts and categories. 

Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new method for discovering disentangled representations, which is a key area of research in AI. 

The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it mentions the evaluation of alternative approaches on disentangling, which is a common problem in NLP. 

Finally, the paper involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a new loss function for training deep embeddings.
